<br>
I struggle with this issue for a couple different reasons.  Initially, I felt kinda bad for the chanter, because I know how I felt when it happened to me (and it has).  Fact is, I had been camping him all evening as well.  Someone was getting a spoon, it boiled down to me.  Amaya's guild did not come to help her.<br>
<br>
1.) I've been camping a spawn (Vessel Drozlin) and had someone else take the kill from me because I didn't have sufficient force in the zone before they did, and thereby lost the kill.  I had to stand there and watch him go down while my group was close.  It's the nature of the race game.   <br>
<br>
2.) The engagement rule .. hmm, I know this is a common practice to engage and kite a mob until you can get sufficient force in zone to kill it.  Personally, I don't engage a mob I can't kill.   I know others do, but I personally don't think its' the right thing to do.  Here's who was online in Unruled Power and their location when this all happened.  It is clear to me that Amaya could not have EVER solo'd Cazel.  It is also clear to me that her guildmates were not mobilizing to assist her.   <br>
<br>
--(60 Assassin) Macvalor (Half Elf): Zone: Maiden<br>
--(60 Virtuoso) Ulwern (Wood Elf): Zone: Burning Wood<br>
--(60 Oracle) Shmeep (Barbarian): Zone: Nexus<br>
--(55 Myrmidon) Korgathe (Iksar): Zone: Oasis<br>
--(Anonymous) Rubiee <br>
--(57 Luminary) Proman (Ogre): Zone: Chardok<br>
--(57 Revenant) Zexu (Dark Elf): Zone: Dreadlands<br>
--(Anonymous) Amaya (was in Oasis fearing Cazel)<br>
--(52 Heretic) Makraiza (Iksar): Zone: Najena <br>
<br>
3.) Had the situation been reversed... I wouldn't have engaged what I couldn't kill.  I'd have called upon my guild for help and kept sight of the target until I could engage it.   Which is what I did in this instance as well.  Had I engaged the giant that I couldn't kill, would UP have killed it?  I sure think so.  <br>
<br>
Amaya and I reached Cazel at about the same time.  He was close to me when he popped.   It is my belief she engaged it when she saw me.  He was not snared at any time, so when she feared it, it took off like a shot and the paladin (non-guildy whom she /ooc'd to come help her)  couldn't keep up with it to do damage.  He was low level paladin as well.  I watched this go on for quite some time, never seeing Cazel go below 99% life.   When Radiant arrived, she was given time to seriously engage.  I'm sorry, but I don't believe anyone would let me kite him around for an hour while they tried to get enough people in zone to kill him.   20 minutes is plenty of time to mobilize a group of people.  Try kiting Lodi around for 20 minutes and see where it gets you.  <br>
<br>
As far as Hate goes, yes they were deliberately training the hell out of Radiant.   But I didn't think Hate was the purpose of this rant.  <br>
<br>
Lastly, I stand by and support the members of my guild.   Flame them.  Flame me.  I know where my friends are at the end of the day.  <br>
