<br>
When my ranger was 20 something and fighting in South Karana many moons ago, there was a bard that would run around and aggro every single gnoll around the paw spires and say he was 'kiting' them, in other words he was engaged with them and killing them.  He was, but so slowly that he made no tangible dent in even one gnoll's health after about 10 minutes of kiting.<br>
<br>
Guess what.  A guide or GM (Can't remember which because I didn't notice such things back then) showed up and /killed every single one of the gnolls he was 'kiting' because he could not possibly kill them and he was disrupting the zone.<br>
<br>
Additionally I have seen guides time and time again specifically state that sufficient force constitutes the right to a monster, not 'snare it and run it around for a while'.  See ragefire disputes in the past when a single druid would snare the human version and run him around while a guild mobilized.  That does not constitute engagement and never has, this is no different.  Sufficient force is not a matter of numbers, it is a matter of ability.  <br>
